---
import Layout from "../layouts/main.astro";
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
import MainNavigation from "../components/navigation/MainNavigation?raw";

const title = "Main Navigation Component";
const description = "Preact has been added as an Astro integration and used for a navigation component.";
---
<Layout
	title={title}
	description={description}>

	<p>
		Main navigation has been added using a <a href="https://preactjs.com/">Preact</a> component. To use Preact we need to add the <a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/integrations-guide/preact/"></a>@astrojs/preact</a> package and update <code>/astro.config.mjs</code>.
	</p>

	<p>The component is used without an Astro <a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/reference/directives-reference/#client-directives">client directive</a>, so it is rendered statically at build time.</p>

	<p>
		The following files have been added: 
	</p>

	<Code lang="text" code={
`📁.
├── 📁 components
│   └── 📁 navigation
│       └ MainNavigation.tsx ➕
│       └ MainNavigation.module.css ➕
├ astro.config.mjs 📝
└ tsconfig.json 📝`} theme="catppuccin-latte">
	</Code>


	<h2>Component View with Raw Import</h2>
	<p>Powered by Vite, the component can be <a href="https://vitejs.dev/guide/assets.html#importing-asset-as-string">imported as a string</a> for viewing in Astro's  <a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/reference/api-reference/#code-">&lt;Code&gt; component.</a></p>
	<Code lang="javascript" code={MainNavigation} theme="catppuccin-latte" />

</Layout>
